reviewText: inventive.  a collection of animated hijinks that balances between comedy science-fiction and romance.  the creators were truly inspired.  a true example of classical action adventure venture.  pure greatness.
This was a strangely addicting series.  Weird but in a good way.  I dismissed it at first, but it grew on me like a giant brain tumor.  Worth a DVD version...but where is it?

This was a really interesting show, probably the best MTV ever made. Too bad they canceled it when the second season came out that when their mission was over which was find special artifacts to save the world from the alien invasion. This show is a hell of a lot better then watching the Real World 24 hours a day. Too me this show was better then Beavis and Butt-Head not that I don't like it it's just that at least these people have sense and their not losers their hero's. And it's still comedy too.

this is the best cartoon i have ever watched. its animation was ahead of its time. the dialogue works very well with the characters supplied. the story lines were social commentary on acceptence. it went off the air a few  years ago, but it is still in my heart. i have searched high and low for  this video. my suggestion is to order this now before it goes out of stock.
